A DEFENDER Babes and Seasider Babes of Lagos will play the opening match as  the 2020 Prudent Energy Handball League begin today  at the Package B of the MKO Abiola Stadium, Abuja. The encounter is slated for 7am ditto for the game involving Rima Strikers and Plateau Vipers (M). In the other games of the day, Imo Grasshoppers will take Kada Queens (F), COAS Shooters lock horns with Borno Spiders (M),    Edo Dynamos battle Safety Babes (F), while Kada Stars and Lagos Seasiders  (Male) fight for the two points at stake. The afternoon session which starts at 3pm will see Niger United takes on defending champions,  Kano Pillars (M) in a grudge game; D: Defenders  battle Safety Shooters (M)  Plateau Peacocks takes on Desert Queens (F), Delta Force and Confluence Stars battle for points (M) , while Adorable Angels tackles Benue Queens (F) in the last game of the day. President of the Handball Federation of Nigeria (HFN),  Sam Ocheho, urged the teams to adhere to the rules guiding the championship even as he commended the sponsor, Prudent Energy for keeping faith with the competition amid  COVID-19 pandemic challenges. “I must commend the sponsor for staying with the HFN despite the economic downturn caused by the pandemic, I will also urge the teams to play by the rules of the game so that the best teams can emerge champions at the end of the competition,” noted Ocheho.